We have successfully passed a constitutional amendment to ban votes of no confidence when a new government cannot be formed. Hopefully this increases the stability of our governments.

@presidential_powers
subtitle: The president can no longer dissolve the Reichstag at will, or call a *Reichsexekution* on state governments.
on-arrival: {!
Q.reform_support = Q.spd_normalized + Q.ddp_normalized + Q.kpd_normalized;
if (Q.z_relation > 49 && (Q.president == "Hindenburg" || Q.president == "Eckener")) {
    Q.reform_support += Q.z_normalized;
} else if (Q.president == "Braun") {
    Q.reform_support += Q.z_normalized - 0.03;
}
!}
view-if: presidential_powers = 0

The wide-ranging presidential powers promised by the constitution are a potential gateway to authoritarianism. Thus, we can support reforms that limit the powers of the president, ending his power to unilaterally terminate an elected government and to remove state governments.

The KPD is in favor of this reform, having been victims of the *Reichsexekution* in the past (when KPD-supported state governments in Thuringia and Saxony were removed). The democrats of the [+ ddp_name +] also support this. [? if president == "Hindenburg": However, the opposition from conservatives is vehement, as they see a reduction in presidential powers as disrespectful to Hindenburg. ?] [? if z_relation <= 49 and president == "Hindenburg" : Thus, the Center Party has been influenced to oppose these reforms. ?] [? if z_relation > 49 and president == "Hindenburg" : Despite this, the Center Party supports the proposed reform. ?] [? if president == "Braun" : The Center Party supports this reform. ?]

- @presidential_powers_2: Call a constitutional referendum to pass the reform!
- @reforms_menu: See other reform options.

@presidential_powers_2
choose-if: reform_support >= pass_threshold
unavailable-subtitle: We do not have enough support for this policy. [? if pro_republic < 65 : We should have an additional margin for the referendum since we need a majority of voters, and many voters who do not support the republic will not participate. ?] [? if z_relation <= 49 and president != "Braun" : The Center Party does not trust us enough to support this policy. ?]
on-arrival: constitutional_reform += 1; presidential_powers = 1
achievement: verfassungsreform

We have successfully passed a constitutional amendment to limit presidential powers! Hopefully this results in a less authoritarian Germany.

@party_bans
subtitle: Create a constitutional court with power to ban anti-constitutional parties.
on-arrival: {!
Q.reform_support = Q.spd_normalized + Q.ddp_normalized;
if (Q.z_relation >= 40) {
    Q.reform_support += Q.z_normalized;
}
if (Q.dvp_relation >= 45) {
    Q.reform_support += Q.dvp_normalized;
}
if (Q.kpd_relation >= 55) {
    Q.reform_support += Q.kpd_normalized * 0.5; // KPD ambivalent
}
// NSDAP and DNVP oppose
if (Q.nsdap_normalized >= 0.15 || Q.dnvp_normalized >= 0.10) {
    Q.reform_support -= 0.05; // Active opposition campaign
}
!}
view-if: constitutional_court = 0

This reform would establish a Constitutional Court (*Verfassungsgericht*) with the power to ban parties that actively work to undermine the democratic order. This is inspired by the lessons of extremist threats to the Republic.

**Support:**
- The [+ ddp_name +] strongly supports this as a defense of democracy.
[? if z_relation >= 40 : - The Center Party supports this reform. ?]
[? if z_relation < 40 : - The Center Party is skeptical - they fear it could be used against Catholic organizations. ?]
[? if !stresemann_dead and dvp_relation >= 45 : - The DVP cautiously supports this as a bulwark against extremism. ?]
[? if kpd_relation >= 55 : - The KPD is ambivalent - they support banning fascists but worry about being targeted themselves. ?]
[? if kpd_relation < 55 : - The KPD opposes this, seeing it as a tool to suppress the revolutionary left. ?]

**Opposition:**
- The NSDAP and DNVP vehemently oppose this, seeing it as an attack on their movements.
- Some in our left wing worry this could be used against us.

**Effect:** Once passed, parties can be banned through legal proceedings if they are proven to be anti-constitutional. The threshold for banning will depend on how democratic the government is.

- @party_bans_2: Call a constitutional referendum to pass the reform!
- @reforms_menu: See other reform options.

@party_bans_2
choose-if: reform_support >= pass_threshold
unavailable-subtitle: We do not have enough support for this policy. [? if pro_republic < 65 : We need a larger margin since many anti-republican voters won't participate. ?] [? if z_relation < 40 : The Center Party doesn't trust us enough. ?]
on-arrival: constitutional_reform += 1; constitutional_court = 1; left_dissent += 5; kpd_relation -= 8 if kpd_relation < 55; kpd_relation += 3 if kpd_relation >= 55; nsdap_relation -= 15; dnvp_relation -= 10; pro_republic += 2;
achievement: verfassungsreform

We have established a Constitutional Court with the power to ban anti-constitutional parties! This is a powerful tool for defending democracy, though it must be used carefully.

@federalism_reform
subtitle: Reduce the power of individual states, strengthen the national government.
on-arrival: {!
Q.reform_support = Q.spd_normalized * 0.8; // Some federalist SPD members oppose
if (Q.ddp_relation >= 40) {
    Q.reform_support += Q.ddp_normalized * 0.7; // DDP has federalist wing
}
if (Q.z_relation >= 50 && Q.z_party_leader != "Kaas") {
    Q.reform_support += Q.z_normalized * 0.6; // Z protective of Catholic states
}
if (Q.kpd_relation >= 50) {
    Q.reform_support += Q.kpd_normalized; // KPD supports centralization
}
// BVP strongly opposes
if (Q.bvp_normalized >= 0.03) {
    Q.reform_support -= 0.08;
}
!}
view-if: federalism_reform = 0

Many believe that the federal structure of Germany, with powerful state governments, creates inefficiency and allows anti-republican forces to entrench themselves in individual states. This reform would:
- Reduce the autonomy of state governments
- Transfer more powers to the national level
- Make it harder for extremists to build regional power bases
- Streamline administration

**Support:**
- The KPD supports this, viewing federalism as reactionary.
- Many in the SPD support this for administrative efficiency.
[? if ddp_relation >= 40 : - The [+ ddp_name +] has mixed feelings but can be convinced. ?]
[? if z_relation >= 50 and z_party_leader != "Kaas" : - The Center Party is cautiously supportive. ?]

**Opposition:**
- The BVP vehemently opposes this as an attack on Bavarian autonomy.
[? if z_party_leader == "Kaas" : - The conservative wing of the Center worries about protecting Catholic regional interests. ?]
- State governments across Germany resist losing power.
- Some federalists in our own party oppose this.

- @federalism_reform_2: Call a constitutional referendum to pass the reform!
- @reforms_menu: See other reform options.

@federalism_reform_2
choose-if: reform_support >= pass_threshold
unavailable-subtitle: We do not have enough support for this policy. [? if pro_republic < 65 : We need a larger margin for the referendum. ?]
on-arrival: constitutional_reform += 1; federalism_reform = 1; bvp_relation -= 20; z_relation -= 8; center_dissent += 8; centralization_progress += 1; prussian_police_strength -= 0.15; spd_prussia = 0
achievement: verfassungsreform

We have passed a constitutional reform reducing state autonomy! The federal government now has greater power to ensure uniform democratic standards across Germany. Bavaria is furious.

@basic_rights
subtitle: Strengthen constitutional guarantees of civil liberties and social rights.
on-arrival: {!
Q.reform_support = Q.spd_normalized;
if (Q.ddp_relation >= 35) {
    Q.reform_support += Q.ddp_normalized;
}
if (Q.z_relation >= 45 && Q.z_party_leader == "Joos") {
    Q.reform_support += Q.z_normalized * 0.8;
} else if (Q.z_relation >= 35) {
    Q.reform_support += Q.z_normalized * 0.5;
}
if (Q.kpd_relation >= 50) {
    Q.reform_support += Q.kpd_normalized * 0.7;
}
!}
view-if: basic_rights_protection = 0

The Weimar Constitution lists many rights, but lacks strong mechanisms to enforce them. This reform would:
- Make basic rights directly enforceable in courts
- Strengthen protections for freedom of speech, assembly, and press
- Guarantee social rights (housing, education, work)
- Protect workers' rights to organize and strike
- Strengthen protections against discrimination

**Support:**
- Strong support from the [+ ddp_name +] and progressive republicans.
[? if z_relation >= 45 and z_party_leader == "Joos" : - The Center Party's progressive wing strongly supports this. ?]
[? if z_relation >= 35 and z_party_leader != "Joos" : - The Center Party gives cautious support. ?]
[? if kpd_relation >= 50 : - The KPD supports this, though they want to go further. ?]

**Opposition:**
- The DNVP opposes expanded rights protections.
- Business interests fear stronger worker protections.
- Conservatives worry about judicial activism.

- @basic_rights_2: Call a constitutional referendum to pass the reform!
- @reforms_menu: See other reform options.

@basic_rights_2
choose-if: reform_support >= pass_threshold
unavailable-subtitle: We do not have enough support for this policy. [? if pro_republic < 65 : We need a larger margin for the referendum. ?]
on-arrival: constitutional_reform += 1; basic_rights_protection = 1; pro_republic += 3; workers_spd += 3; unemployed_spd += 2; new_middle_spd += 2; dvp_relation -= 8; dnvp_relation -= 12; labor_strength += 5;
achievement: verfassungsreform

We have strengthened constitutional protections for basic rights! Germany now has some of the most progressive civil liberties protections in Europe.

@as_is
go-to: root



@ban_party_menu
title: Party Banning Powers
subtitle: Use the Constitutional Court to ban anti-democratic parties
new-page: true
view-if: constitutional_court = 1 and spd_in_government = 1 and justice_minister_party = "SPD" and (constitutional_reform_timer = 0 or constitutional_reform_timer <= -6)
on-arrival: month_actions += 1; constitutional_reform_timer = 12

= Party Banning

With the Constitutional Court now established, we have the legal power to initiate proceedings to ban parties that actively work against the democratic constitutional order.

However, this is an **extremely serious** decision. Banning a party:
- Requires substantial legal evidence of anti-constitutional activity
- Needs political support from coalition partners
- Can provoke violent backlash if the party is popular
- May be seen as authoritarian if used carelessly

Which party, if any, should we move to ban?

- @ban_nsdap_menu: Consider banning the NSDAP
- @ban_dnvp_menu: Consider banning the DNVP
- @ban_kpd_menu: Consider banning the KPD
- @review_evidence: Review evidence against each party
- @reforms_menu: Do not pursue any bans at this time
- @easy_discard

@review_evidence

**NSDAP Evidence:**
[? if sa_banned = 0 and sa_strength > 100 : ✓ Maintains illegal paramilitary (SA) - strong evidence ?]
[? if sa_banned = 1 : ✗ SA already banned - less evidence available ?]
[? if nsdap_putsch_seen or beer_hall_seen : ✓ History of coup attempts - strong evidence ?]
[? if nsdap_normalized >= 0.25 : ⚠ Very popular (25%+) - banning extremely risky ?]
[? if nsdap_normalized >= 0.15 and nsdap_normalized < 0.25 : ⚠ Popular (15-25%) - banning risky ?]
[? if nsdap_normalized < 0.15 : ✓ Limited support - banning more feasible ?]
[? if hitler_deported : ✓ Leader deported for anti-state activity - evidence ?]

**DNVP Evidence:**
[? if dnvp_line = 3 and sh_banned = 0 and sh_strength > 50 : ✓ Collaborates with illegal paramilitaries - evidence ?]
[? if dnvp_line = 3 and dnvp_relation_nsdap >= 60 : ✓ Alliance with NSDAP - evidence of anti-democratic intent ?]
[? if dnvp_line = 1 : ✗ Westarp line is constitutionally loyal - **cannot ban** ?]
[? if dnvp_line = 2 : ⚠ Traditional conservatives - weak case, politically dangerous ?]
[? if dnvp_coup_seen or kapp_seen : ✓ Involved in coup attempts - strong evidence ?]

**KPD Evidence:**
[? if rfb_banned = 0 and rfb_strength > 100 : ✓ Maintains illegal paramilitary (RFB) - evidence ?]
[? if kpd_party_leader = "Thälmann" : ✓ Moscow-directed, rejects democracy - evidence ?]
[? if kpd_party_leader = "Conciliators" : ⚠ Reformist leadership - weak case ?]
[? if communist_coup_seen or red_rising_seen : ✓ History of insurrections - strong evidence ?]
[? if kpd_relation >= 50 : ⚠ Good relations - banning would destroy united front ?]
[? if kpd_normalized >= 0.20 : ⚠ Very popular - banning extremely risky ?]

- @ban_party_menu: Back to decision

@ban_nsdap_menu
go-to: nsdap_ban_check

Should we initiate proceedings to ban the NSDAP?

@nsdap_ban_check
on-arrival: {!
    // Calculate support for banning NSDAP
    Q.ban_support = 0;
    Q.evidence_strength = 0;
    Q.political_cost = 0;
    
    // Evidence calculation
    if (Q.sa_banned == 0 && Q.sa_strength > 100) {
        Q.evidence_strength += 3;
    }
    if (Q.nsdap_putsch_seen || Q.beer_hall_seen) {
        Q.evidence_strength += 3;
    }
    if (Q.hitler_deported) {
        Q.evidence_strength += 2;
    }
    if (Q.sa_militancy >= 0.5) {
        Q.evidence_strength += 2;
    }
    
    // Political support calculation
    Q.ban_support = Q.spd_normalized;
    
    if (Q.z_relation >= 55 && Q.nsdap_normalized < 0.15) {
        Q.ban_support += Q.z_normalized;
    } else if (Q.z_relation >= 45 && Q.nsdap_normalized < 0.10) {
        Q.ban_support += Q.z_normalized * 0.7;
    }
    
    if (Q.ddp_relation >= 40) {
        Q.ban_support += Q.ddp_normalized;
    }
    
    if (Q.dvp_relation >= 50 && Q.nsdap_normalized < 0.12 && !Q.stresemann_dead) {
        Q.ban_support += Q.dvp_normalized * 0.6;
    }
    
    if (Q.kpd_relation >= 50) {
        Q.ban_support += Q.kpd_normalized * 0.8;
    }
    
    // Popularity penalty
    if (Q.nsdap_normalized >= 0.25) {
        Q.ban_support -= 0.15;
        Q.political_cost = 3;
    } else if (Q.nsdap_normalized >= 0.15) {
        Q.ban_support -= 0.08;
        Q.political_cost = 2;
    } else {
        Q.political_cost = 1;
    }
    
    // Pro-republic threshold
    Q.ban_threshold = 0.50;
    if (Q.pro_republic < 65) {
        Q.ban_threshold = 0.58;
    }
    if (Q.pro_republic < 55) {
        Q.ban_threshold = 0.65;
    }
    
    // Can we ban?
    Q.can_ban_nsdap = (Q.evidence_strength >= 5 && Q.ban_support >= Q.ban_threshold);
!}

**Banning the NSDAP:**

**Evidence Strength:** [+ evidence_strength +]/10
[? if evidence_strength < 5 : ⚠ Evidence is weak - court may reject the case. ?]
[? if evidence_strength >= 5 and evidence_strength < 7 : ✓ Sufficient evidence to proceed. ?]
[? if evidence_strength >= 7 : ✓ Strong evidence - compelling case. ?]

**Political Support:** [+ (ban_support * 100).toFixed(1) +]%
Required: [+ (ban_threshold * 100).toFixed(1) +]%

**Coalition Support:**
- SPD: Supporting
[? if z_relation >= 55 and nsdap_normalized < 0.15 : - Center: Supporting ?]
[? if z_relation >= 45 and z_relation < 55 and nsdap_normalized < 0.10 : - Center: Cautiously supporting ?]
[? if z_relation < 45 or nsdap_normalized >= 0.15 : - Center: Opposed or abstaining ?]
[? if ddp_relation >= 40 : - [+ ddp_name +]: Supporting ?]
[? if ddp_relation < 40 : - [+ ddp_name +]: Hesitant ?]
[? if dvp_relation >= 50 and !stresemann_dead : - DVP: Cautiously supporting ?]
[? if kpd_relation >= 50 : - KPD: Supporting ?]
[? if kpd_relation < 50 : - KPD: Will not coordinate with us ?]

**Risks:**
[? if nsdap_normalized >= 0.25 : - ⚠⚠⚠ NSDAP very popular - **HIGH RISK OF CIVIL WAR** ?]
[? if nsdap_normalized >= 0.15 and nsdap_normalized < 0.25 : - ⚠⚠ NSDAP popular - risk of major unrest and violence ?]
[? if nsdap_normalized < 0.15 : - ⚠ Risk of SA underground resistance and terrorism ?]
[? if sa_strength > 200 : - ⚠⚠ SA is strong - expect violent resistance ?]
[? if sa_strength > 400 : - ⚠⚠⚠ SA is very strong - civil war likely ?]

- @ban_nsdap_confirm: Proceed with banning the NSDAP
- @ban_party_menu: Reconsider

@ban_nsdap_confirm
choose-if: can_ban_nsdap
unavailable-subtitle: [? if evidence_strength < 5 : Not enough evidence. Need to document more anti-constitutional activities. ?] [? if ban_support < ban_threshold : Not enough political support. Need better relations with coalition partners. ?]

This is an extremely serious decision. Are you certain?

- @ban_nsdap_execute: Yes, ban the NSDAP
- @ban_party_menu: No, reconsider

@ban_nsdap_execute
on-arrival: {!
    Q.nsdap_banned = 1;
    Q.ban_party_timer = 24; // Can't ban another party for 2 years
    
    // Violence response based on strength
    if (Q.nsdap_normalized >= 0.25 || Q.sa_strength > 400) {
        Q.nsdap_ban_violence = 3; // Civil war likely
        Q.sa_strength *= 0.3; // SA goes underground
        Q.sa_militancy += 0.5;
    } else if (Q.nsdap_normalized >= 0.15 || Q.sa_strength > 200) {
        Q.nsdap_ban_violence = 2; // Major unrest
        Q.sa_strength *= 0.2;
        Q.sa_militancy += 0.3;
    } else {
        Q.nsdap_ban_violence = 1; // Resistance but containable
        Q.sa_strength *= 0.1;
        Q.sa_militancy += 0.2;
    }
    
    // Political effects
    Q.pro_republic += 5;
    Q.nationalism -= 10;
    
    // Coalition reactions
    if (Q.z_relation >= 45) {
        Q.z_relation += 5;
    } else {
        Q.z_relation -= 10; // Worried about authoritarianism
    }
    
    Q.ddp_relation += 8;
    Q.dvp_relation -= 5;
    Q.kpd_relation += 10;
    
    if (Q.dnvp_line === 3) {
        Q.dnvp_relation -= 20;
    }
    
    // Voter redistribution
    Q.workers_dnvp += Q.workers_nsdap * 0.3;
    Q.workers_other += Q.workers_nsdap * 0.2;
    Q.workers_spd += Q.workers_nsdap * 0.1;
    Q.workers_nsdap *= 0.4; // Some stay loyal underground
    
    Q.old_middle_dnvp += Q.old_middle_nsdap * 0.4;
    Q.old_middle_dvp += Q.old_middle_nsdap * 0.2;
    Q.old_middle_other += Q.old_middle_nsdap * 0.1;
    Q.old_middle_nsdap *= 0.3;
    
    Q.new_middle_dnvp += Q.new_middle_nsdap * 0.3;
    Q.new_middle_dvp += Q.new_middle_nsdap * 0.2;
    Q.new_middle_ddp += Q.new_middle_nsdap * 0.15;
    Q.new_middle_nsdap *= 0.35;
    
    Q.rural_dnvp += Q.rural_nsdap * 0.4;
    Q.rural_other += Q.rural_nsdap * 0.2;
    Q.rural_nsdap *= 0.4;
    
    Q.unemployed_kpd += Q.unemployed_nsdap * 0.2;
    Q.unemployed_other += Q.unemployed_nsdap * 0.3;
    Q.unemployed_nsdap *= 0.5;
    
    Q.catholics_z += Q.catholics_nsdap * 0.3;
    Q.catholics_other += Q.catholics_nsdap * 0.2;
    Q.catholics_nsdap *= 0.5;
!}
go-to: nsdap_banned_aftermath

The Constitutional Court has banned the National Socialist German Workers' Party!

@nsdap_banned_aftermath
go-to: nsdap_ban_civil_war if nsdap_ban_violence >= 3; nsdap_ban_unrest if nsdap_ban_violence == 2; nsdap_ban_resistance if nsdap_ban_violence == 1

@nsdap_ban_civil_war
on-arrival: civil_war_seen = 1; in_civil_war = 1

⚠⚠⚠ **CIVIL WAR**

The banning of the NSDAP has triggered a massive violent response. SA units across Germany have risen in armed rebellion. The Reichswehr is mobilizing, but street battles rage in multiple cities.

This is a fight for the survival of the Republic.

- @civil_war: Continue...

@nsdap_ban_unrest
on-arrival: crisis_urgency += 2; sa_strength += 50; strife += 2

**Major Unrest**

The NSDAP ban has triggered widespread violence. SA paramilitaries have attacked government buildings, fought street battles with the Reichsbanner and police, and assassinated several prominent republicans.

The SA has gone underground but remains dangerous. We must remain vigilant.

- @root: Continue...

@nsdap_ban_resistance
on-arrival: sa_strength += 20; strife += 1

**Underground Resistance**

The NSDAP ban has been implemented with relative success. While there are reports of SA cells operating underground and isolated acts of terrorism, the Nazi movement has been largely suppressed.

Democracy in Germany is safer, though eternal vigilance is required.

- @root: Continue...

@ban_dnvp_menu
go-to: dnvp_ban_check

Should we initiate proceedings to ban the DNVP?

@dnvp_ban_check
on-arrival: {!
    Q.ban_support = 0;
    Q.evidence_strength = 0;
    
    // Can only ban Hugenberg DNVP
    if (Q.dnvp_line === 1) {
        Q.can_ban_dnvp = false; // Westarp line is constitutional
        Q.ban_reason = "westarp_constitutional";
    } else {
        // Evidence
        if (Q.dnvp_line === 3 && Q.sh_banned == 0 && Q.sh_strength > 50) {
            Q.evidence_strength += 3;
        }
        if (Q.dnvp_line === 3 && Q.dnvp_relation_nsdap >= 60) {
            Q.evidence_strength += 2;
        }
        if (Q.dnvp_coup_seen || Q.kapp_seen) {
            Q.evidence_strength += 4;
        }
        if (Q.sh_militancy >= 0.4) {
            Q.evidence_strength += 2;
        }
        
        // Support
        Q.ban_support = Q.spd_normalized;
        
        if (Q.z_relation >= 50 && Q.dnvp_line === 3) {
            Q.ban_support += Q.z_normalized * 0.5;
        }
        
        if (Q.ddp_relation >= 45) {
            Q.ban_support += Q.ddp_normalized * 0.8;
        }
        
        if (Q.kpd_relation >= 50) {
            Q.ban_support += Q.kpd_normalized;
        }
        
        Q.ban_threshold = 0.52;
        if (Q.pro_republic < 65) {
            Q.ban_threshold = 0.60;
        }
        
        Q.can_ban_dnvp = (Q.evidence_strength >= 6 && Q.ban_support >= Q.ban_threshold);
    }
!}

go-to: dnvp_westarp_cannot_ban if dnvp_line == 1; dnvp_ban_show if dnvp_line != 1

@dnvp_westarp_cannot_ban

**Banning the DNVP:**

**⚠ CANNOT BAN**

Kuno von Westarp's DNVP has accepted the constitutional order and operates within democratic norms. Banning them would be a flagrant abuse of power and destroy our credibility.

The Constitutional Court would reject this case immediately.

- @ban_party_menu: Back

@dnvp_ban_show

